
1) Get Centos image from: https://cloud.centos.org/centos/7/images/CentOS-7-x86_64-GenericCloud.qcow2
2) Create ssh key pair using ssh-keygen. Do not create the keypair in Symphony UI
3) Update terraform.tfvars
4) Run TF
5) Reboot Master, Worker and Infra through Symphony UI. This will cause update of metadata server
6) After reboot Openshift nodes require reinit of their hostnames
   a)  run ./set_hostname.sh from this folder
7) ssh into the Bastion node and run:
   >> ansible-playbook /home/centos/openshift_ansible_3_11/playbooks/prerequisites.yml -i /home/centos/ansible-hosts --key-file=/home/centos/.ssh/<KP file> --ssh-common-args='-o StrictHostKeyChecking=no'
   >> ansible-playbook /home/centos/openshift_ansible_3_11/playbooks/deploy_cluster.yml -i /home/centos/ansible-hosts --key-file=/home/centos/.ssh/<KP file> --ssh-common-args='-o StrictHostKeyChecking=no'
8) After installation is completed set the admin account in Openshift master.
   a) run ./set_admin.sh from this folder
9) Log in to the Openshift console with admin account
   https://console.<master ip>.xip.io:8443
